Description: Limestone ostracon: on the recto four incomplete lines of an unknown literary text, probably a hymn (to the Nile?). On the verso three lines of text containing words only (a school exercise?).
Bibliographic references: Trismegistos / An interdisciplinary portal of papyrological and epigraphic resources (136390) (http://www.trismegistos.org/text/136390)
